TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Stochastic Optimal Control Technique for Models with Estimated Coefficients
AU  - Craine, Roger
AU  - Havenner, Arthur
AB  - ["If one is willing to interpret Q̃ [the Goldberger, Nagar, Odeh reduced form coefficient covariance estimate] as a covariance matrix of the random parameter π around the constant <tex-math>$\tilde{\pi}$</tex-math>, rather than as a covariance matrix of the random estimates <tex-math>$\tilde{\pi}$</tex-math>, then using <tex-math>$\tilde{\pi}$</tex-math> for <tex-math>$\tilde{\pi}$</tex-math> and Q̃ for Q <tex-math>$[\tilde{\pi}$</tex-math> and Q are the mean and covariance matrix of the random parameter π] will provide an approximate solution to the evaluation of expectations required in our optimal control problem" [3, p. 641], italics added).]
